Sentencas: High-temperature electrical conductivity and electrochemical activity in the oxygen redox reaction of Sr2FeCo0.5Mo0.5O6-delta (SFCM) and Sr1.6La0.4FeCo0.5Mo0.5O6-delta (LSFCM) at variable oxygen partial pressure have been studied.
Titulo: High-temperature electrical conductivity and electrochemical activity in oxygen redox reaction of La-doped Sr2FeCo0.5Mo0.5O6-δ

Sentencas: We have found that the partial replacement of Sr2+ by La3+ results in a substantial decrease in the total electrical conductivity due to a decrease in the hole charge carrier concentration.
Titulo: High-temperature electrical conductivity and electrochemical activity in oxygen redox reaction of La-doped Sr2FeCo0.5Mo0.5O6-δ

Sentencas: Detailed analysis of the high- and low-frequency parts of the impedance spectra at pO(2) = 0.1-1 atm and 873-1173 K has revealed different rate-limiting steps in the oxygen redox reaction for SFCM and LSFCM resulted from different oxygen vacancy concentrations in these materials.
Titulo: High-temperature electrical conductivity and electrochemical activity in oxygen redox reaction of La-doped Sr2FeCo0.5Mo0.5O6-δ

Sentencas: For SFCM, the oxygen redox reaction is limited by the processes of adsorption and dissociation of oxygen molecules, while for LSFCM by the charge transfer occurring at the triple phase boundary.
Titulo: High-temperature electrical conductivity and electrochemical activity in oxygen redox reaction of La-doped Sr2FeCo0.5Mo0.5O6-δ
